					<description><![CDATA[“Nativity II.” All images © Althea Crome, shared with permission Have you ever sent a knit sweater through a dryer cycle and returned to find it a fraction of the size it once was? Well, think even smaller. Althea Crome’s incredibly detailed miniature sweaters didn’t shrink in a dryer but were instead created stitch by [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>
<div id="attachment_246801" style="width: 1450px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246801" class="wp-image-246801 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-2-e1714753554100.jpg" alt="a miniature knit cardigan inspired by Gerard David's &quot;The Nativity with Donors and Saints Jerome and Leonard.&quot;" width="1440" height="1488" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-2-e1714753554100.jpg 1440w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-2-e1714753554100-640x661.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-2-e1714753554100-960x992.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 1440px) 100vw, 1440px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246801" class="wp-caption-text">“Nativity II.” All images © Althea Crome, shared with permission</p>
</div>
<p>Have you ever sent a knit sweater through a dryer cycle and returned to find it a fraction of the size it once was? Well, think even smaller. <a href="https://www.altheacrome.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Althea Crome</a>’s incredibly detailed miniature sweaters didn’t shrink in a dryer but were instead created stitch by stitch with scrupulous dexterity over hundreds of hours.</p>
<p>The Indiana-based fiber artist began knitting in college and refined her skills by frequenting knitting shops. Crome was eager to learn new methods, and like many who are part of knitting communities, the artist was happily welcomed with advice, knowledge, and guidance. Mastering one technique meant moving onto another, and when it came to constantly challenging herself, Crome always rose to the occasion.</p>
<p>As time went on, she eventually found herself in the throes of micro-knitting. For Crome, there was something particularly stimulating and liberating about knitting small. Designing tiny garments and being able to knit them relatively quickly provided instant gratification. As she continued to create increasingly small and detailed pieces, her practice began to evolve.</p>
<p> </p>
<div id="attachment_246809" style="width: 1930px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246809" class="wp-image-246809 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-13.jpg" alt="a miniature knit cardigan inspired by Van Gogh's &quot;Starry Night&quot;" width="1920" height="1256" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-13.jpg 1920w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-13-640x419.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-13-960x628.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-13-1536x1005.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246809" class="wp-caption-text">“Starry Night”</p>
</div>
<p>In comparison to the average knit sweater that holds about four to eight stitches per inch, Crome has achieved a gauge of more than 80 stitches per inch, meticulously entwining extremely fine silk in different hues. For “Nativity II,” the artist blended over 70 individual colors of thread to achieve detailed shading effects.</p>
<p>Crome is inspired by iconic works such as <a href="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/tags/vincent-van-gogh/">Van Gogh</a>’s “Starry Night,” ancient Greek amphoras, and Warhol’s soup cans. Before starting each miniature garment, she first designs her own pattern, then she works underneath a high-powered magnifier, using minuscule knitting needles that she made herself from high-tensile-strength surgical steel.</p>
<p>“We’re always looking at other people’s art, trying to understand it,” Crome says. “Taking those images and working with a different medium, I just want to dig in further than my eyes. I want to dig in with my hands.” This way, the artist feels closer to the works that influence her, contemplating ideas for some time before testing new skills and bridging the gap between conceptual ideas and physical manifestation.</p>
<p>Find more of Crome’s work on her <a href="https://www.altheacrome.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">website</a>.</p>
<p> </p>
<div id="attachment_246806" style="width: 2010px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246806" class="wp-image-246806 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-12.jpg" alt="detail of a miniature knit cardigan inspired by Van Gogh's &quot;Starry Night&quot;" width="2000" height="1360" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-12.jpg 2000w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-12-640x435.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-12-960x653.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-12-1536x1044.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246806" class="wp-caption-text">“Starry Night”</p>
</div>
<div id="attachment_246803" style="width: 1930px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246803" class="wp-image-246803 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-9.jpg" alt="a miniature knit sweater in the shape of an Ancient Greek amphora" width="1920" height="1439" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-9.jpg 1920w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-9-640x480.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-9-960x720.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-9-1536x1151.jpg 1536w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-9-285x214.jpg 285w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246803" class="wp-caption-text">“Ancient Greek Amphora I”</p>
</div>
<div id="attachment_246804" style="width: 1930px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246804" class="wp-image-246804 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-10.jpg" alt="a miniature knit cardigan inspired by Picasso" width="1920" height="1760" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-10.jpg 1920w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-10-640x587.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-10-960x880.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-10-1536x1408.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246804" class="wp-caption-text">“Picasso, Woman in a Yellow Hat”</p>
</div>
<div id="attachment_246811" style="width: 1930px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246811" class="wp-image-246811 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crrome-warhol.jpg" alt="a miniature knit cardigan inspired by Warhol's soup cans" width="1920" height="960" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crrome-warhol.jpg 1920w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crrome-warhol-640x320.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crrome-warhol-960x480.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crrome-warhol-1536x768.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246811" class="wp-caption-text">“Pop Art Cardigan”</p>
</div>
<div id="attachment_246802" style="width: 1930px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246802" class="wp-image-246802 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-3.jpg" alt="a miniature knit cardigan inspired by Gerard David's &quot;The Nativity with Donors and Saints Jerome and Leonard.&quot;" width="1920" height="1524" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-3.jpg 1920w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-3-640x508.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-3-960x762.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-3-1536x1219.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246802" class="wp-caption-text">“Nativity II”</p>
</div>
<div id="attachment_246807" style="width: 1930px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246807" class="wp-image-246807 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-14.jpg" alt="three miniature knit sweaters worn on three fingers to show scale" width="1920" height="1628" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-14.jpg 1920w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-14-640x543.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-14-960x814.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-14-1536x1302.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246807" class="wp-caption-text">“Sheep Farm” series</p>
</div>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-246808" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-15.jpg" alt="Process photo of sewing miniature knitting" width="2000" height="1735" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-15.jpg 2000w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-15-640x555.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-15-960x833.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crome-15-1536x1332.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px"></p>
